main event: A woman in Jersey City, New Jersey reported observing an unidentified object in the sky on August 6, 1964.
interesting points: The object appeared to be moving slowly and silently across the sky in a northerly direction.
The object appeared to have colored lights around the edge or perimeter.
The woman became quite excited and disturbed by the sighting and immediately contacted the New Jersey State Police, who in turn notified the U.S. Air Force.
The U.S. Air Force representative responded to the scene and interviewed the witness and obtained photographs she had taken of the object.
The photographs submitted were inconclusive and did not clearly show the object the witness reported observing.
sighted object: a bright, shiny object with colored lights around the edge or perimeter
